# Customer — Internal Endpoints
# UC-021: BFF resolves which tenants a Google account belongs to
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. pnpm infra:up           (start PostgreSQL + Pub/Sub emulator)
#   2. pnpm --filter @beloauto/backend run migration:run
#   3. pnpm --filter @beloauto/backend run dev
#
# REST Client environment: select "local" in VS Code status bar

@baseUrl     = {{backendUrl}}
@internalKey = {{$dotenv INTERNAL_API_KEY}}
@sub         = google-sub-customer-a

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HAPPY PATH
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all tenants for a known Google OAuth ID (single tenant → returns 1 entry)
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/tenants?googleOAuthId={{sub}}
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###

### Get all tenants for an unknown Google OAuth ID (returns empty array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/tenants?googleOAuthId=unknown-sub-xyz
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###

### UC-023 — Get all tenants for a customer by customerId + current tenantId (switch-tenant flow)
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/{{customerId}}/tenants?tenantId={{tenantId}}
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ERROR CASES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 401 — Missing X-Internal-Key (global guard)
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/tenants?googleOAuthId={{sub}}

###

### 400 — Missing googleOAuthId query parameter
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/tenants
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###

### 400 — Missing tenantId query parameter for by-id tenants lookup
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/{{customerId}}/tenants
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###

### 404 — Customer not found for given customerId + tenantId
GET {{baseUrl}}/internal/customers/00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000009999/tenants?tenantId={{tenantId}}
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}
